  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Diagnostic errors have been reported frequently in patient with pulmonary embolism since
      symptoms are not specific. However, there is only scarce evidence that the delay associated
      with diagnostic errors may impact patient prognosis. The aim of this study is to determine
      the frequency of diagnostic errors and if they are associated with more severe pulmonary
      embolism in term of initial presentation and complications.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
